The setting you&#39;re looking for is &#39;parallelQueues&#39; on the 
QueueAssignmentPolicy. It&#39;s discussed here:

https://webarchive.jira.com/wiki/display/Heritrix/H3+Dev+Notes+for+Crawl+Operators#H3DevNotesforCrawlOperators-QueueAssignmentPolicies%3A%27parallelQueues%27and%27deferToPrevious%27settings

Because of the potential for such parallel collection to be disruptive, 
this setting should be used very carefully, and only for sites where you 
have permission to crawl aggressively.

There&#39;s an example of its use targeted at two specific domains (so that 
the global defaults for all other sites can remain at usual levels of 
politeness) in the H3 User Manual page about settings overlay Sheets:

https://webarchive.jira.com/wiki/display/Heritrix/Sheets

- Gordon @ IA

